article.headline: Albertsons stock falls 3% then rises as trading begins
article.body: Shares of Albertsons Cos. Inc. ACI, +1.71% began trading on Friday and immediately sank 3% before rising 0.6%. The first trade was at 11:33 a.m. ET for $15.50. The grocer priced last night at $16, below the sought-after $18-20 range. The decades-old company went public at a time when grocery demand is high due to the coronavirus pandemic, and after first filing then pulling a previous IPO. The Renaissance IPO ETF IPO, +1.98% has gained 29.2% for the year to date while the S&P 500 index SPX, +0.87% is down 6.1% for the period.
